<!-- WHAT IS EPOXY GROUT -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">What Is Epoxy Grout?</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">If you've only ever had standard cement grout in your shower, here's what makes epoxy grout fundamentally different &mdash; and why it outperforms cement in every wet-area metric.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-primary mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">water_drop</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">100% Waterproof</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Epoxy grout is made from resin, not cement. It cures into a solid, non-porous material that doesn't absorb a single drop of water. Standard cement grout is like a sponge by comparison &mdash; it soaks up moisture and holds it against your tiles.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-primary mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">opacity</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Stain-Proof</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Because epoxy grout is non-porous, nothing can soak into it. Soap scum, body oils, hair dye, hard water minerals &mdash; they all sit on the surface and wipe straight off. Your grout lines stay the same colour for years, not weeks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-primary mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">cleaning_services</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Highly Mould-Resistant</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Mould needs moisture to grow. Since epoxy grout doesn't absorb water, mould has nowhere to take root. No more scrubbing black spots off your grout lines every few weeks &mdash; the surface stays clean with normal shower use.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-primary mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">shield</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Chemical Resistant</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Epoxy grout resists acids, alkalis, and harsh cleaning products that break down cement grout over time. You can clean your shower with virtually any household cleaner without damaging the grout &mdash; though you'll rarely need to.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

